(1989) Regulations purporting to create a newspaper exception from the statutory newsprint exception are beyond the scope of this statute and the authority of the Director of Revenue, and, therefore, a nullity. Hearst Corp. v. Director of Revenue, 779 S.W.2d 557 (Mo. banc).

